'${prop}': must be a positive integer.\\\")\\n   490\\t        }\\n   491\\t        if (value <= 0) {\\n   492\\t            throw new GradleException(\\\"Invalid -P${propertyName}='${prop}': must be >= 1.\\\")\\n   493\\t        }\\n   494\\t    }\\n   495\\t    return value\\n   496\\t}\\n   497\\t\\n   498\\t/*\\n   499\\t * Helper utilities for environment setup, and backup/restore\\n   500\\t * used by testMetadataGeneration.\\n   501\\t */\\n   502\\tdef withUnsetTckDir(List<String> baseArgs) {\\n   503\\t    if (System.getProperty(\\\"os.name\\\").toLowerCase().contains(\\\"windows\\\")) {\\n   504\\t        [\\\"cmd.exe\\\", \\\"/d\\\", \\\"/c\\\", \\\"set GVM_TCK_TCKDIR= && \\\" + baseArgs.join(' ')]\\n   505\\t    } else {\\n   506\\t        [\\\"/usr/bin/env\\\", \\\"-u\\\", \\\"GVM_TCK_TCKDIR\\\"] + baseArgs\\n   507\\t    }\\n   508\\t}\\n   509\\t\\n   510\\tdef backupDirIfExists(File srcDir, File backupDir) {\\n   511\\t    boolean had = srcDir?.isDirectory()\\n   512\\t    if (had) {\\n   513\\t        backupDir.parentFile?.mkdirs()\\n   514\\t        project.copy {\\n   515\\t            from(srcDir)\\n   516\\t            into(backupDir)\\n   517\\t        }\\n   518\\t    }\\n   519\\t    had\\n   520\\t}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge5/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.apache.maven:maven-api-plugin:4.0.0-rc-5/local-ci-fixup/test-infra-2026-05-08T13-32-27-948564Z.log:21:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_11\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba build.gradle | sed -n '325,430p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"   325\\tdef runGradleTaskAndCheck(List<String> args, String label, File logFile) {\\n   326\\t    int exit = runLoggedCommand(args, label, logFile, project.rootDir)\\n   327\\t    if (exit != 0) {\\n   328\\t        throw new GradleException(\\\"${label} failed with exit code ${exit} (see ${logFile})\\\")\\n   329\\t    }\\n   330\\t    return exit\\n   331\\t}\\n   332\\t\\n   333\\t/**\\n   334\\t * Runs generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix and returns the log file.\\n   335\\t *\\n   336\\t * @param gradleCmd   Gradle executable path (e.g., \\\"./gradlew\\\" or \\\"gradlew.bat\\\")\\n   337\\t * @param logsDir     Directory where the log will be written\\n   338\\t * @return            The File pointing to the generated matrix log\\n   339\\t */\\n   340\\tdef runGenerateMatrixAndCheck(String gradleCmd, File logsDir) {\\n   341\\t    logsDir.mkdirs()\\n   342\\t    def logFile = new File(logsDir, \\\"generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix.log\\\")\\n   343\\t    runGradleTaskAndCheck(\\n   344\\t        [gradleCmd, \\\"generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix\\\"],\\n   345\\t        \\\"generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix\\\",\\n   346\\t        logFile\\n   347\\t    )\\n   348\\t    return logFile\\n   349\\t}\\n   350\\t\\n   351\\t/**\\n   352\\t * Executes an external command, logs its output to both the console and a dedicated file,\\n   353\\t * and returns the exit code. Prepends and appends custom headers and footers to the log\\n   354\\t * indicating success or failure.\\n   355\\t *\\n   356\\t * Behavior:\\n   357\\t * - Prints a header to both console and log file before running the command.\\n   358\\t * - Ensures parent directories for the log file exist, and overwrites the file with the header.\\n   359\\t * - Runs the provided command in a specified working directory, logging both stdout and stderr to the file.\\n   360\\t * - Waits for the process to finish and captures its exit code.\\n   361\\t * - Appends a footer line to both console and log to indicate SUCCESS or FAILURE, including the exit code if failed.\\n   362\\t * - Returns the process exit code to the caller.\\n   363\\t *\\n   364\\t * @param args      The command as a list of strings (executable plus arguments).\\n   365\\t * @param label     A label for this invocation, included in the header/footer.\\n   366\\t * @param logFile   File to which all output is logged (will be created/overwritten).\\n   367\\t * @param workingDir Directory in which to execute the process.\\n   368\\t * @return          The exit code of the process.\\n   369\\t */\\n   370\\tdef runLoggedCommand(List<String> args, String label, File logFile, File workingDir) {\\n   371\\t    def startTime = new Date().format(\\\"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\\\")\\n   372\\t    def header = \\\"==== [${startTime}] BEGIN ${label} logged at ${logFile.absolutePath}\\\"\\n   373\\t    println(header)\\n   374\\t    if (logFile?.parentFile) {\\n   375\\t        logFile.parentFile.mkdirs()\\n   376\\t    }\\n   377\\t    logFile.text = header + System.lineSeparator()\\n   378\\t\\n   379\\t    def pb = new ProcessBuilder(args as String[])\\n   380\\t    pb.directory(workingDir)\\n   381\\t    String nativeImageMode = resolveSelectedNativeImageMode()\\n   382\\t    if (nativeImageMode != null && !nativeImageMode.trim().isEmpty()) {\\n   383\\t        pb.environment().put(\\\"GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE\\\", nativeImageMode)\\n   384\\t    }\\n   385\\t    pb.redirectErrorStream(true)\\n   386\\t    pb.redirectOutput(ProcessBuilder.Redirect.appendTo(logFile))\\n   387\\t    def proc = pb.start()\\n   388\\t    int exit = proc.waitFor()\\n   389\\t\\n   390\\t    def endTime = new Date().format(\\\"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\\\")\\n   391\\t    def footer = exit != 0\\n   392\\t            ? \\\"==== [${endTime}] END   ${label} FAILURE (exit ${exit}) logged at ${logFile.absolutePath}\\\"\\n   393\\t            : \\\"==== [${endTime}] END   ${label} SUCCESS logged at ${logFile.absolutePath}\\\"\\n   394\\t\\n   395\\t    if (exit != 0) {\\n   396\\t        println(\\\"Failure log for ${label}\\\")\\n   397\\t        try {\\n   398\\t            if (logFile?.exists()) {\\n   399\\t                logFile.eachLine { println(it) }\\n   400\\t            } else {\\n   401\\t                println(\\\"(log file not found)\\\")\\n   402\\t            }\\n   403\\t        } catch (Throwable e) {\\n   404\\t            println(\\\"Error reading ${logFile}: ${e.message}\\\")\\n   405\\t        }\\n   406\\t    }\\n   407\\t\\n   408\\t    logFile.append(footer + System.lineSeparator())\\n   409\\t    println(footer)\\n   410\\t    return exit\\n   411\\t}\\n   412\\t\\n   413\\t/**\\n   414\\t * Runs a set of external commands concurrently using the provided ExecutorService, writing\\n   415\\t * per-command logs under build/command-logs and aggregating failures.\\n   416\\t *\\n   417\\t * Behavior:\\n   418\\t * - Submits each command to the pool via submit(Callable) and waits for all futures to complete.\\n   419\\t * - Shuts down the pool and awaits termination for up to 1 hour.\\n   420\\t * - On any non-zero exit, prints a summary and the contents of the failed logs, then throws a GradleException.\\n   421\\t * - On success, prints a summary message indicating the logs directory.\\n   422\\t *\\n   423\\t * @param coordinate A label used for log file names and messages (e.g., an artifact coordinate or a batch like 1/64).\\n   424\\t * @param commands   List of maps representing commands to run; each entry must contain:\\n   425\\t *                   - name: String task label (e.g., \\\"checkstyle\\\")\\n   426\\t *                   - args: List<String> full process arguments passed to ProcessBuilder\\n   427\\t * @param pool       ExecutorService used to run the commands concurrently; this method will call\\n   428\\t *                   shutdown() and awaitTermination(...) on it.\\n   429\\t * @throws GradleException if any command exits with a non-zero status.\\n   430\\t */\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge5/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.apache.maven:maven-api-plugin:4.0.0-rc-5/local-ci-fixup/test-infra-2026-05-08T13-32-27-948564Z.log:23:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_12\",\"t